review_blob: A bit lighter in flavor and palate then I expected but still a enjoyable beer.  Good color and sustained head.  The malts were a bit sweet on the sweet side.  I would drink this again.

Im not the biggest fan of Imp. Stouts but this is certainly a well made beer.  Very intense smokey coffee flavor, noticable hops, and aftertaste is espresso.  The bitterness is a bit too much for my liking but I would definately drink this beer again.  (I better, I have 3 left)
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: I couldnt finish a bottle of this beer.  Flat and bitter tasting, this is one of the few beers I would never drink again.  I thought I would like the rich malts and roasted soba flavor...I was very wrong.
beer_name: Rogue Morimoto Black Obi Soba Ale

review_blob: This is the first time Ive seen this season beer at the brewery.  Its a far cry from a Samuel Adams Oatmeal Stout.  Good creamy head and retention.  Aroma was very malty with a mouth watering apperance.  Still, it came up very short in flavor.  Its flavor is best described as simple and flat.  Nothing going on here.  I enjoy a good stout and its lackluster flavor and overly bitter/burnt finish left a lot to be desired.
Nice mild yeast aroma....malts add to an enjoyable sweetness.  Possibly a bit too sweet for me.  Light on the palate....reminds me of apricots.  Its a decent beer.

Hey,  Lance Armstrong lives by this beer!  Good enough for him, good enough for me.  Well, its nothing fancy.  Sweet, dark, somewhat flat in flavor.  Nothing special but it does the job and it goes down well.  It goes in my stand-by catagory.  Possibly a bit too expensive for a decent Texas beer.  Good beer for a BBQ and a nice steak.

Aroma is noted with apricots and peach.  Didnt pour a particulary nice head.  Flavor is quite sweet and fruity.  Good hints of peppery  yeast but plesantly balanced.  A bit thin on the palate but pleasing.  A good punch of alcohol finish.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: This is one good looking beer.  Pours a  deep carmel color with a booming cream head.  Nice yeast aroma with hints of cloves (as advertised).  Flavor is bold with carmel tones, good alcohol, and mild fruit.  Nice malt balance. Love the sour finish.  No heavy linger on the palate.  This is my first Weizen Bock....and very good.

This beer definately has its place:  when you cant get your girlfriend/wife to drink beer with you.  Ill admit, I enjoyed the first few sips of this beer.  Hey, I like blueberries!  But what happened to the rest of the beer?  Its more watery and thin then my pound and ground Miller Lite!  Now, its not terrible at all.  A real hot day....sitting by the pool..... and you girlfriend ran out of liquor....give her one of these "wine coolers".  Ill finish off my 6 pack and that will be my only experience with this beer.
beer_name: Sea Dog Wild Blueberry Wheat Ale

review_blob: Not a big favorate of mine.  I dont like the malt/hops balance here.  I like a nice hop flavor but this just doesnt do it for me.  Ill pass on this one everytime (unless Im completely out of beer)

Another great stand by beer for me.  Lacks the head frothy head I like but its certainly makes up for in flavor.  A bit dull on the palate and a few extra hops would make this a perfect brewed brown ale for me.  Nevertheless, I wont walk away from this one.
A great stand by beer.  Its balanced well and not too acidic.  Hops are a bit light for me but its excellent daily drinking beer.
I apprecaite this beer for being brewed well but it just doesnt do it for me.  Aroma is weak and I really dont get it all the hype.

I know many people like this beer but it doesnt work for me.  I find it difficult to drink and find its flavor somewhat confusing and complex.  Sure, there is a lot going on here but just doesnt satisfy my taste.  Technically, it a good beer but not my cup of tea at all.

I liked the way it smelled initially.  I was completely surprised by the burnt malt flavor.  The more I drank it, the more I thought about something definately wrong here.  It doesnt look all that bad in the glass but I was more interested in drinking it.  It tastes like it was fermented in an old attic!  Okay, now my taste buds are going numb and it feels like someone put out a camp fire in my mouth.  I still like the aroma and its doing its job....getting me a bit buzzed so i dont realize its not the best beer around but at 5 bucks a 6pack....its working.
beer_name: Main Street Beer Dergys Amber Ale

review_blob: UPDATED: APR 27, 2005

An even flavored light nutty beer.  A hint of carmel, its very light on the palate.  No bursting of flavor here.  Its smooth but nothing extraordinary.  I drank this beer around 55F to get the most of its flavor.  Not a favorate but I woulnt pass on it.

An extremely well balanced beer.  Ive had the bleu a long time ago and tasting it again.  I do like the banana and hint of clove.  Nothing stands out too much.  What I do like about this beer is that its complex flavor that leaves you guessing its ingredients.  The alcohol is hidden well.  I wouldnt consider bringing a 6-pack of this too a football game but it would pair  well with beer and chicken.

I enjoy how this beer feels on the palate....very light a bit oily.  I feel the flavor is complete and nothing extra, nothing missing.  Its balanced well.  The apricot flavor is most predominate and not overwhelming.
UPDATED: MAY 7, 2005
Not a very good IPA at all.  Little complexity and a whole lot of bitterness.  Lacks the fine aroma of good hops.
Not a big fan of this beer.  I do love my stout but this one is too bitter for me.  Not smooth enough.  I can see how people would like this beer but its just too bitter and "burnt" for me.

Taste about the same as a flat Newcastle....but I do like Newcastle.  Typical flavor for the style.  Nothing extravagant here but a very pleasing beer.  Not too sweet, nice mixture of malt, very low hop....balanced well.  I could get several of these down and might just do so again.

This Brown ale confuses me a bit.  I just finished a Dogfish Chicory Stout and except for the Chicory and a bit more hops, Im seeing the same beer.  Burnt coffee flavor, chocolate.  The hops are certainly not hiding in this brown ale.  A bit too sweet for me.  Nothing wrong here except perhaps originality.

Im happy with this beer.  I dont normally like fruity flavors but the whole package just sits well with me.  Nothing stands out on its own here.  Everything is balanced and combind to produce a very good beer.  I like this a bit on the cold side.  I have nothing negative to say about this beer.  Its not my first choice but it certainly will quench your thirst.
UPDATED: APR 24, 2005

I thought this was a bold flavor but Im sitting here trying my first Dogfish Brown and it taste rather similar with out the chicory flavor.  Maybe my taste buds suck but seems to taste like they started out and flavored quite similar.  Its worth picking up a few.

Kind of wants to be an IPA but not quite there yet.  Big floral boquet but not without the pronounced major high notes such as rosemary or pine.  Silky smooth on the tounge, a bite of a sharp aftertaste.
Super smooth, nice looking beer.  Impressed by the immediate fruity flavor...carmel, grapes.  Havent had a "sweet" brown ale that wasnt too sweet.  This is pleasant.
I like this beer ....maybe not as much as the 90 but its certainly a bit smoother.  Lacks a bit of that pine flavor i really like in the 90.  Im happy with the hop content.
Just add some olive oil and youll have a nice balsamic salad dressing.  Dark cherry after taste.  A bit too sweet for my liking.  Does get better towards the bottom of the bottle.

Im giving this beer a 5 for very personal reasons.  Before I was turned on to craft beers, Miller lite was my "get your drunk on" beer.  Sure, you have to drink it a degree or two above freezing to avoid its real taste.  Sure, without the added "beer smell", you would think youre drinking water.  Still, when youre looking for something really light, not looking to fall asleep after several, and dont care that the craft beer community thinks youre an idiot for drinking this one......its a perfect choice.
A beautiful looking beer.  Tremendous light brown, creamy, head....awesome lacing.  Hint of initial sweetness.  Moderate bitter roasted coffee finish.  I think I smell soy sauce floating in there!

Pours a nice yellow with a fizzy off white head....desent lacing.  Aroma is strong hops and yeast.  (suppose to have a citrus/orange notes that my I couldnt pick up due to my terrible sense of smell.)  Its refreshing, light and lively.  Found it a bit acidic for my liking but worth having for a hot summers day.
Lively and refreshing citrus flavor.  Fizzy head with very light lacing.  Hoppy aroma, mildly yeasty...strong orange notes.  Extremely light on the palate with a dry finish.

Good looking murky brown beer with fizzy carbination.  Fluffy/frothy light brown head with descent lacing.  Carmel aroma is most prodominent.  Strong honey flavor with a modest bitter finish.  Smooth and light on the palate...noticable alcohol.

Not much bad to say about this beer.  It says drink me as all the Sam Smiths do.  Very little hoppy taste.  Malty and yummy.  I like this beer a bit warmer then recommended.  Very light and easy on the palate...watery finish.  No lingering aftertaste.  Only negative is that I just drank my last one!

I dont know what to think of this beer.  Frothy head, avg. lacing...diminished quickly.  I dont get a good aroma here.  Alcohol smell but not overpowering.  Flavor is fair.  A bit bitter and tangy.  Hints of sweetness.  A rather complex flavor and beer for that matter.  Prodominent yeast flavor.  Im not a huge fan here...but not bad.
UPDATED: JUN 13, 2004

Disappointing head.  This beer visually is like most of the Youngs beers...blah.  Aroma is faint.  Yes, dark chocolate is prominant but lacks a good aroma.     The appearance is quite lackluster.  Still, I was impressed with its flavor.  A moderately sweet taste that doesnt change and is short lived.  Its rather light to the palate with a creamy texture.  Carbonation is rather flat and a chalky finish.  Yet, I find myself really liking this beer.  It doesnt have all the attribute of a brillant beer but in terms of flavor, its quite good.  Note, my second pour produced a much better head although it diminished rather quickly.

Im not the biggest hops fan as I prefer to lean toward the sweeter side of     malt.  Still, The aroma was unreal.  A beautiful frothy head that had a very pleasing hoppy aroma.  Extreme cloves comes to mind.  The initial flavor was a bit overwheling for me (too hoppy) but doesnt linger for too long.  The finish is soft and sweet.  You certainly can feel the 9% ABV half way through.  The strong hops flavor reminds me of the same hoppy flavor s at American micro breweries.  As the beer warmed up to 60F, hops flavor mellowed and I really enjoyed this beer.

I wish i could say more about this beer but it seems rather "flat" to me.    What you taste initially is what you taste in the end.  No highs or lows.  Almost perfectly PH blanced.  Im most impressed by the smokey aftertaste.  Mesquite?  BBQ?...I just keep thinking I want to throw a steak on the grill!  Soy sauce!  When this beer warms up...soy/teriaki sauce is all i can think of.  Its positive.  Pair this with a steak on the grill....perfect!

Carmel aroma prominent yet has difficulty identifying   the boquet.  The appearance is rather blah!  Similar to Youngs Double Chocholate, but this has a less creamier head.  A fruity taste as well, but cannot pick out flavors.  Its sweet!!  No lingering aftertaste.  Watery to the palate and the finish is clean..maybe a bit dry.  I didnt think i would like this beer initially but as it warms up, its flavors tremendously awaken.  Sweet and earthy...thoughts of wheat.  Im impressed but this is an ocassional beer best after a cold winter night.

Love this stuff!  You sure this is beer?  Champaign maybe?  Fruity/citrus aroma.  Appears light yellow and a bubbly white head.  Unfortunately, the head dissapates rather quickly but never the less....very tasty.  Very light on the palate....little after taste.  A slight astringent finish.  Again, tastes light a descent champaign to me...and i love it.
